result.execSummary:
The defendant Daniel J Getchell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Def in court.  Justine L Suleski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
P O Matthew Teachout
Court: This is a request by the DOC to extend the Defendant's probation so he can pay the Costs
and so he can complete the DOMAB.
Def - Object, I started the DOMAB in August 2016, I only missed one class.
The ATTIC did not have a facilitator for alot of the classes so they cancelled the classes.
That is no fault of mine.  As of now, I have completed 37 or 38 groups, my probation is done in April,
I will have 45 groups done by then.
Court: What about the $935.00 you owe?
Def - I have been laid off since November, I currently receive Unemployment.
I pay Child Support.  I qualify for Food Stamps, Badger Care.  I feel Food and a place
to stay is more important.  I just started back to work today for the Season.  I was under
the understanding from Mr Teachout that I would discharge as planned and this would be
converted to a civil judgment...
Suleski - The Domestic Violence is The Most important part of his Probation.  I did not know about the contact
he had, there was some Police Contact.  I think this should be extended for him to complete the DOMAB.
COURT: That was the Court's intention as well at Sentencing, for you to complete the DOMAB.
PROBATION IS EXTENDED UNTIL 07-21-17 OR UNTIL THE SUCCESSFUL COMPLETION OF THE DOMAB PROGRAM,
WHICH EVER COMES FIRST.  That will also give you some time to pay on those costs you owe.
Def - I just want to make sure it is very clear that it is just until the DOMAB is done.
Court: This is just until the DOMAB is completed, there is not a request to extend it until you 
have paid off the costs, although you do need to make payments.
Teachout - Once you have completed the Program, you need to let the Judge know, then it will be up
to the Judge to give you the early discharge.  We will send a form to the Court.
